Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.11,0:06:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}火星探测器{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to the probes exploring Mars...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.07,0:06:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}3个多小时 到卡西尼土星探测器{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}more than three hours to Cassini at Saturn...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.70,0:06:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}超过29小时 到旅行者1号{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and over 29 hours to Voyager 1, the most distant of all...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.70,0:06:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那是现在所到达的太阳系最远的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}now heading out of the solar system.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不过这些距离在宇宙尺度上是微不足道的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Still, these distances are trivial on a cosmic scale.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.67,0:07:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们几乎可以理解地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We can almost understand the 10 billion miles...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.63,0:07:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}与旅行者号之间的100亿英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}separating Earth from Voyager...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.14,0:07:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是接下去呢?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but what's next?{\r}
