Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.52,0:07:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在近25万亿英里外{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}nearly 25 trillion miles away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.31,0:07:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}25后面有12个0{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's 25 followed by 12 zeroes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.23,0:07:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我通常被问及一个问题 你作为天文学家 怎么能够{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I am often asked a question, "How can you, as an astronomer...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}真正理解这些庞大的距离{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}"really comprehend these vast distances...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.36,0:07:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些庞大的数字?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}" these huge numbers?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.61,0:07:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}答案是 我不能{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And the answer is, l can't.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.83,0:07:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}人的大脑真的折腾不起这么大的数字{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The human brain really doesn't wrap itself around numbers that big.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}偶尔 我会写出N多个0{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Occasionally, I actually write out...{\r}
