Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}只是为了看看那个数字有多大{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}just to see how huge that number is.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.05,0:07:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不过现实中 当然啦 作为天文学家{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But in reality, of course, as astronomers...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.21,0:07:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们会花上一整天来写0{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we would be spending all day writing zeroes...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.01,0:07:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}除非找到更好的单位来使用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}unless we came up with a better unit to use...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那就是光年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that's what a light-year is.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.72,0:07:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}一光年约等于6万亿英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A light-year is approximately 6 trillion miles.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.93,0:08:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就是光走上一年的距离{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's the distance that light travels in one year.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.02,0:08:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}用光年来描述距离{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Using light-years to describe distances...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.77,0:08:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}打开了光速特性的另一个尺度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}opens up another dimension of light speed's character.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.06,0:08:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}来看看 天狼星 天上最亮的恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Think of it. Sirius, the brightest star in the sky...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.53,0:08:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在8.6光年外{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is 8.6 light-years away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.11,0:08:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那就意味着我们所见到的 不是它今天的模样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That means we see it, not as it is today...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.78,0:08:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而是它8.6年前的模样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but as it was 8.6 years ago.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.33,0:08:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们看到的明亮的织女星是25年前的模样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We see the bright star Vega as it was 25 years ago...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.29,0:08:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}红巨星参宿四的模样是500年前的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the red super giant Betelgeuse as it was 500 years ago.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.63,0:08:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它是大自然的精美礼物{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's a wonderful gift of nature...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.89,0:08:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为它传播需要时间 所以我们就能够回眸过去{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that because it takes time to travel, we're able to look back in time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.93,0:08:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们看得越远 回眸的时间也就越早{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The further out we look in distance, the further back in time we look.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们将无法知道我们宇宙的历史是怎么回事{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We would have no idea what our cosmic history was...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.94,0:08:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果光速稍纵即逝的话{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}if the speed of light traveled instantaneously.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.28,0:08:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}劳拉.丹妮是著名的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Laura Danly is curator...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.61,0:08:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}洛杉矶格里菲斯天文台台长{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of the historic Griffith Observatory in Los Angeles.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.74,0:09:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}由于光能够将我们带到过去{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}With light's ability to take us into the past...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.41,0:09:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}她汇集了一叠照片{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}she's assembled a stack of photos...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}讲述光速的宇宙快照故事{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that tell light speed's story of the universe in snapshots...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.83,0:09:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}把时间倒回其地点{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}looking back in time to its beginning...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.09,0:09:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}距今130多亿年前{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}more than 13 billion years ago to the present day.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.80,0:09:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我汇总成一本{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I'm putting together a scrapbook...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.80,0:09:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们星系家族史的剪贴本{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of the history of our family of galaxies...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.72,0:09:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我挑选出我们所有能用望远镜看到的星系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and I chose all the galaxies that we can see with our telescopes...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.56,0:09:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}也就是我们望远镜所能看到的最早的情形{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as far back as we can see with our telescopes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.69,0:09:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}剪贴本里每一幅照片 显示了宇宙中的方方面面{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Each photo in this album, then, shows something in the universe...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.11,0:09:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}倒转的时光相当于以光年计的距离{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with a look-back time equivalent to its distance in light-years.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.99,0:09:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}著名的蟹状星云 6500年前{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The famous Crab Nebula, 6,500 years ago...{\r}
