Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.50,0:16:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就是宇宙的整个大小{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is the entire size of the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.84,0:16:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}事实上 它有可能要比这大得多{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In fact, it might be much bigger than that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.92,0:16:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那只是指 光旅行时间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's just that, with light travel time...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.30,0:16:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是我们所能见到的整个范围 那就是我们的视界{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that's all we can see. That's our horizon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.76,0:16:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}细细想想这个谜题吧{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So, consider this conundrum.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.14,0:17:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}位于我们视界边缘的一个星系里的天文学家{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Astronomers in a galaxy at one edge of our horizon...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.31,0:17:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是不可能看到我们视界另一头的任何星系的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}can't possibly see any galaxies on the other edge of our horizon...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.15,0:17:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是他们可以看到另一个方向的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but they can see galaxies...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.69,0:17:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}135亿光年里的星系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}13 1/2 billion light-years in the other direction...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.65,0:17:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而在他们自己视界边缘的天文学家就有可能了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and so can astronomers at the edge of their horizon...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.86,0:17:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如此以往 或许就是无限远{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and on and on, perhaps to infinity.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.95,0:17:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}至于地球上的天文学家 光速将他们困住了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As for astronomers on Earth, light speed has them trapped.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.66,0:17:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果我们要问我们光视界之外的事情{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}lf we ask what is happening beyond our light horizon...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.96,0:17:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们就不得不面对这样的事实{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we have to face the fact...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.13,0:17:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就是光速确实是个障碍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that the speed of light really is a barrier.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.21,0:17:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们从未见到过我们视界之外的任何东西{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We've never seen anything beyond our light horizon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.84,0:17:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们会沉湎于{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Can we take comfort in the fact...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.47,0:17:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这张壮观的照片{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that there is so much to see inside our horizon{\r}
